<paragraph blockId="0.[813,1425,382,1976]" pageId="0" pageNumber="1942">
This species differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Hansf." authorityName="Hansf." class="Asteroidea" family="Asterinidae" genus="Asterina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1942" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="micheliae">
<emphasis box="[1192,1417,1800,1827]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1942">Asterina micheliae</emphasis>
Hansf.
</taxonomicName>
reported on 
<taxonomicName box="[1026,1242,1838,1864]" genus="Michelia" kingdom="Plantae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1942" rank="species" species="nilagirica">
<emphasis box="[1026,1242,1838,1864]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1942">Michelia nilagirica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1309,1417,1838,1864]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="0" pageNumber="1942">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hansford, G. C." box="[820,1002,1875,1901]" pageId="0" pageNumber="1942" pagination="28 - 50" refId="ref1531" refString="Hansford, G. C. (1947). New or interesting tropical fungi I. Proceedings of the Linnaean Society of London 158: 28 - 50." type="journal article" year="1947">Hansford 1947</bibRefCitation>
) in having typical thyriothecium and differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hosagoudar &amp; Riju" authorityYear="2011" box="[1020,1195,1912,1939]" class="Asteroidea" family="Asterinidae" genus="Asterina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1942" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="micheligena">
<emphasis box="[1020,1195,1912,1939]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1942">A. micheligena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having straight mycelium and larger ascospores.
</paragraph>
